1
00:00:05,672 --> 00:00:07,273
Sorry, I have to go.

2
00:00:07,941 --> 00:00:09,175
You didn't used to be like this.

3
00:00:10,777 --> 00:00:13,046
You never helped me when I needed it.

4
00:00:16,549 --> 00:00:17,950
YU
13 MISSED CALLS

5
00:00:17,951 --> 00:00:19,219
YU

6
00:00:22,622 --> 00:00:24,157
Stop this, Sora.

7
00:00:26,793 --> 00:00:28,128
- What the hell, damn it!
- Sora!

8
00:00:30,930 --> 00:00:32,098
What are you doing?

9
00:00:34,034 --> 00:00:35,335
Shut up!

10
00:00:37,904 --> 00:00:40,806
- Sora.
- This is none of your business.

11
00:00:40,807 --> 00:00:41,641
Go away!

12
00:00:56,689 --> 00:00:57,590
Yu.

13
00:01:12,972 --> 00:01:13,872
MIDDLE SCHOOL GRADUATION PARTY

14
00:01:13,873 --> 00:01:16,042
Hey, where's Tatsuki?

15
00:01:16,609 --> 00:01:18,410
He rushed out in a panic.

16
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:20,246
Did something happen?

17
00:01:20,947 --> 00:01:21,781
Not sure.

18
00:01:27,387 --> 00:01:28,955
- Hello?
<i>- Tatsuki?</i>

19
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:30,857
What happened?

20
00:01:32,559 --> 00:01:33,526
Are you okay?

21
00:01:48,308 --> 00:01:49,375
Thanks for coming.

22
00:01:50,343 --> 00:01:51,444
No problem at all.

23
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:52,779
Please come in.

24
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,914
Excuse me.

25
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:57,884
Hello.

26
00:01:58,384 --> 00:02:01,488
This is Mr. Mikumo, the representative,
and my co-worker Ms. Shizuku.

27
00:02:04,457 --> 00:02:06,259
Sorry for coming all of a sudden.

28
00:02:07,494 --> 00:02:09,329
I heard about what happened.

29
00:02:10,163 --> 00:02:11,131
Are you okay?

30
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:14,167
Yes.

31
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:18,437
Would you like to consult
a specialist about this?

32
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:19,572
No.

33
00:02:21,541 --> 00:02:23,308
In situations like this,

34
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:25,712
it's advised to put some distance
between both parties.

35
00:02:26,913 --> 00:02:29,549
Would you like to come over
to Yukanai right now?

36
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:31,317
What?

37
00:02:32,018 --> 00:02:33,652
But Sora is…

38
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:37,490
We will stay here and be with Sora.

39
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:39,058
Yes.

40
00:02:55,708 --> 00:02:57,544
YUKANAI

41
00:02:58,411 --> 00:02:59,479
Hey.

42
00:02:59,979 --> 00:03:00,879
Hello.

43
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,982
Come in. Sorry for the mess.

44
00:03:03,550 --> 00:03:04,717
I'm Fujinaga.

45
00:03:05,285 --> 00:03:06,286
I'm Ajicchan.

46
00:03:06,786 --> 00:03:09,121
I bet you guys are hungry.

47
00:03:09,122 --> 00:03:10,523
Want some sandwiches?

48
00:03:11,424 --> 00:03:12,292
Want some?

49
00:03:12,825 --> 00:03:13,893
Please don't mind me.

50
00:03:15,161 --> 00:03:17,162
I have some <i>takoyaki</i> mix left.

51
00:03:17,163 --> 00:03:18,864
Let's have <i>takoyaki!</i>

52
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:21,901
Let me see if we have octopus.

53
00:03:23,069 --> 00:03:23,937
This way.

54
00:03:35,114 --> 00:03:36,182
How long has it been

55
00:03:38,017 --> 00:03:40,186
since Sora started becoming
physically violent

56
00:03:41,354 --> 00:03:42,455
like that?

57
00:03:46,326 --> 00:03:48,595
I think after the suicide attempt.

58
00:03:55,201 --> 00:03:56,970
I don't understand why

59
00:03:57,971 --> 00:03:59,639
he did something like that.

60
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:03,109
I see.

61
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:07,547
And after that,
he barely came out of his room anymore

62
00:04:08,314 --> 00:04:10,149
<i>and he got more and more irritable.</i>

63
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:15,088
I just didn't know what to do,

64
00:04:15,688 --> 00:04:17,390
and when I tried talking
he just yelled at me.

65
00:04:18,891 --> 00:04:20,693
Then he started lashing out at things.

66
00:04:21,794 --> 00:04:23,795
Stop. Stop it.

67
00:04:23,796 --> 00:04:26,766
- Stop it.
- Let go of me! Get away!

68
00:04:33,206 --> 00:04:34,540
<i>Ever since then,</i>

69
00:04:36,042 --> 00:04:38,211
whenever something
rubbed him the wrong way, he'd…

70
00:04:52,025 --> 00:04:54,027
I failed to notice what was happening.

71
00:04:57,697 --> 00:04:58,965
I'm sorry.

72
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:04,070
I thought about confiding in you,

73
00:05:05,071 --> 00:05:06,271
<i>but the timing was never right.</i>

74
00:05:06,272 --> 00:05:08,041
SORRY, I CAN'T MAKE IT JUST YET

75
00:05:08,841 --> 00:05:10,576
<i>And you always seemed to be busy.</i>

76
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:14,747
Plus, I had decided
to raise him on my own,

77
00:05:15,782 --> 00:05:17,282
so relying on anyone else

78
00:05:17,283 --> 00:05:19,952
felt like I'd be admitting my failure,
and I couldn't do that.

79
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:24,557
But in the end…

80
00:05:25,558 --> 00:05:26,492
No.

81
00:05:28,628 --> 00:05:31,631
Ultimately, it's all my fault.

82
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,375
What should we do?

83
00:05:48,414 --> 00:05:52,285
All right!
Here's Ajicchan's special <i>takoyaki.</i>

84
00:05:53,586 --> 00:05:55,787
You might not be
in the mood for it right now,

85
00:05:55,788 --> 00:05:56,622
but please enjoy.

86
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:00,960
We have a sleeping bag for guests,
so please use it.

87
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:05,098
Stay the night. You can take a bath too.

88
00:06:06,299 --> 00:06:07,199
But…

89
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:10,536
Professor and Shi-chan will handle things
back at your house.

90
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:12,105
Okay?

91
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:16,109
I'll leave you to take care of the rest.

92
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:17,744
Okay.

93
00:06:18,945 --> 00:06:20,113
Thank you.

94
00:06:27,286 --> 00:06:28,387
Okay.

95
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:31,556
Apparently, we're free to use
whatever ingredients are in the fridge.

96
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:32,392
Thanks.

97
00:06:32,892 --> 00:06:34,192
Can you get the plates out?

98
00:06:34,193 --> 00:06:35,027
Okay.

99
00:06:36,929 --> 00:06:40,499
I can only hope that it will be
to you and Sora's liking.

100
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,769
- Do you cook often?
- Yes.

101
00:06:43,269 --> 00:06:44,436
I sure do.

102
00:06:44,437 --> 00:06:46,439
I only make simple things though.

103
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:52,644
I wonder if Ms. Yu ever consulted
with the police

104
00:06:52,645 --> 00:06:54,547
or the local authorities?

105
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:59,452
She was probably shouldering it
all on her own.

106
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:01,687
I bet.

107
00:07:02,188 --> 00:07:05,057
Ms. Yu's safety is what matters most.

108
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:08,194
They'll have to discuss
the best course of action.

109
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:10,663
It won't be an easy task.

110
00:07:12,131 --> 00:07:14,933
It's ready.

111
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:17,203
- Please taste it, Shi-chan.
- Okay.

112
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:22,809
It's good.

113
00:07:30,716 --> 00:07:31,784
Sora.

114
00:07:32,351 --> 00:07:34,453
I work with your dad
at the alternative school.

115
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,788
My name is Mikumo.

116
00:07:36,489 --> 00:07:37,824
Sorry for coming all of a sudden.

117
00:07:40,226 --> 00:07:43,396
Everyone, including Ms. Shizuku and I,

118
00:07:44,263 --> 00:07:45,765
are on your side.

119
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:48,367
Please believe that.

120
00:07:50,837 --> 00:07:53,940
But can I just say one thing?

121
00:07:55,374 --> 00:07:59,278
No matter the circumstances,
violence is never right.

122
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:03,449
Unless you stop being violent,

123
00:08:04,283 --> 00:08:07,086
your mom will never be able
to come back home.

124
00:08:08,521 --> 00:08:10,156
We wouldn't want that, would we?

125
00:08:14,126 --> 00:08:15,361
Anyway…

126
00:08:18,064 --> 00:08:21,300
Aren't you hungry?

127
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:25,972
I made some fried rice.
I'll leave it outside the door.

128
00:08:45,157 --> 00:08:46,926
Wow.

129
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,195
MATERNAL AND CHILD HEALTH HANDBOOK

130
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:53,799
They look so happy.

131
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:55,501
Look at those smiling faces.

132
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:59,505
Mr. Tatsuki had black hair back then?

133
00:09:00,773 --> 00:09:01,973
Yeah.

134
00:09:01,974 --> 00:09:04,544
He dyed it to that milk tea color
after working at Yukanai.

135
00:09:05,278 --> 00:09:06,379
Milk tea, huh?

136
00:09:09,649 --> 00:09:10,850
Shi-chan…

137
00:09:11,417 --> 00:09:12,251
Yes?

138
00:09:12,985 --> 00:09:16,188
I can handle the rest on my own,
so you can head home for today.

139
00:09:17,123 --> 00:09:18,456
But…

140
00:09:18,457 --> 00:09:21,060
While you're at it,
I'd like you to stop by Yukanai too.

141
00:09:23,329 --> 00:09:24,163
Okay.

142
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:30,736
- Sorry for causing you trouble.
- It's okay.

143
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:32,938
How's Sora doing?

144
00:09:32,939 --> 00:09:36,107
Professor is staying close to him,

145
00:09:36,108 --> 00:09:37,143
so please be rest assured.

146
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:38,910
Okay.

147
00:09:38,911 --> 00:09:42,280
These are the photos of Sora,
and some of his artwork

148
00:09:42,281 --> 00:09:44,483
I contacted you about borrowing
a little while ago.

149
00:09:45,051 --> 00:09:46,018
Why did you bring these?

150
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:48,653
Professor Mikumo

151
00:09:48,654 --> 00:09:50,889
wanted the two of you to see them.

152
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:52,924
I really want Tatsuki and Ms. Yu

153
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:54,860
to give "sharing" a try with these.

154
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:57,029
Sharing?

155
00:09:59,231 --> 00:10:02,268
As the two of them look back
on their shared memories together,

156
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:05,571
something just might come into view.

157
00:10:11,711 --> 00:10:12,545
Okay.

158
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:15,548
Then I'll be going now.

159
00:10:16,549 --> 00:10:17,550
Thank you.

160
00:10:28,327 --> 00:10:29,527
MATERNAL AND CHILD HEALTH HANDBOOK

161
00:10:29,528 --> 00:10:30,663
SORA

162
00:10:32,131 --> 00:10:33,833
He was so small.

163
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:37,637
When we brought him home
for the first time,

164
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:40,239
he was so tiny and fragile,

165
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:43,274
I remember feeling anxious,
wondering if we'd be able

166
00:10:43,275 --> 00:10:44,176
to raise him properly.

167
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:08,868
Where was this?

168
00:11:10,536 --> 00:11:12,571
The open space at Hayama Zoo.

169
00:11:14,607 --> 00:11:16,841
We went because he said
he wanted to see giraffes,

170
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:18,710
but it was bigger than he expected

171
00:11:18,711 --> 00:11:20,680
so he got scared
and kept bawling the whole time.

172
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,982
I don't remember that…

173
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:36,295
Remember this?

174
00:11:38,898 --> 00:11:41,400
Sorry, I don't remember…

175
00:11:44,070 --> 00:11:45,705
You've forgotten all the family outings?

176
00:11:47,907 --> 00:11:49,241
I wonder why.

177
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:52,111
You were so engrossed with work.

178
00:11:52,678 --> 00:11:54,680
You were rarely home
on the weekends either.

179
00:12:04,924 --> 00:12:07,059
I'm not in any of these pictures.

180
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:12,098
Sora and I often went out,
just the two of us.

181
00:12:22,308 --> 00:12:23,175
Look at this.

182
00:12:25,878 --> 00:12:27,113
Sora

183
00:12:27,613 --> 00:12:30,750
wasn't good at putting his feelings
into words, but…

184
00:12:32,551 --> 00:12:34,053
When I look at his drawings,

185
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:38,357
I feel like I can somehow grasp
what he was trying to say.

186
00:12:40,693 --> 00:12:41,594
Yeah.

187
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:54,607
What's that?

188
00:12:55,808 --> 00:12:58,978
It's from when he stopped going to school
soon after entering middle school.

189
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:19,064
Sora.

190
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:22,434
Sora.

191
00:13:30,509 --> 00:13:32,178
<i>Back then,</i>

192
00:13:33,112 --> 00:13:36,282
I kept on telling myself
that it was all to help Sora,

193
00:13:37,917 --> 00:13:40,419
but I was ignoring his feelings,
and pushing him into a corner.

194
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,086
Sora.

195
00:13:42,087 --> 00:13:44,190
Staying holed up like that
won't solve anything.

196
00:13:45,724 --> 00:13:47,525
- Come out here.
- No.

197
00:13:47,526 --> 00:13:48,961
Stop it.

198
00:13:50,629 --> 00:13:51,564
Sora!

199
00:13:53,766 --> 00:13:56,202
No wonder he can't forgive me.

200
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:05,978
I never consulted with you,

201
00:14:07,313 --> 00:14:08,414
and acted selfishly.

202
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:14,086
And yet,

203
00:14:16,422 --> 00:14:18,224
I left you alone to deal with it.

204
00:14:19,825 --> 00:14:21,427
I'm really sorry.

205
00:14:47,119 --> 00:14:48,454
You were still drawing this?

206
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:56,328
Sora loved this beach.

207
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:16,348
Do you…

208
00:15:18,951 --> 00:15:19,952
remember this?

209
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:27,793
It's the seashell Sora found for me.

210
00:15:30,396 --> 00:15:32,197
Here, this is for you.

211
00:15:34,566 --> 00:15:35,667
- It's pretty.
- Right?

212
00:15:35,668 --> 00:15:36,834
Thanks.

213
00:15:36,835 --> 00:15:38,203
Okay, Dad, let's race.

214
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:52,851
You still have it?

215
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:06,165
Where did things go wrong?

216
00:16:26,285 --> 00:16:28,520
I'm worried about Sora,
so I'll go back home.

217
00:16:29,555 --> 00:16:30,489
Should I go too?

218
00:16:31,690 --> 00:16:32,524
It's okay.

219
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,701
Okay, got it.

220
00:16:49,908 --> 00:16:51,042
Good morning.

221
00:16:51,043 --> 00:16:52,511
Hold on, Sora.

222
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:56,281
Who are you?

223
00:16:59,351 --> 00:17:01,720
I'm Mikumo,
the one who made that fried rice.

224
00:17:02,788 --> 00:17:04,156
Why are you still here?

225
00:17:04,656 --> 00:17:05,524
Sorry.

226
00:17:06,625 --> 00:17:08,594
I was worried about leaving you all alone.

227
00:17:10,596 --> 00:17:12,698
- How annoying.
- Hey, Sora.

228
00:17:15,401 --> 00:17:18,003
Do you want to try going to Yukanai?

229
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:19,571
What?

230
00:17:20,072 --> 00:17:20,972
He's there, right?

231
00:17:20,973 --> 00:17:22,941
Your dad? Yeah, he'll be there.

232
00:17:25,477 --> 00:17:26,478
I don't want to see him.

233
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:28,280
I see.

234
00:17:30,616 --> 00:17:31,717
What are

235
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:34,887
your feelings towards your dad right now?

236
00:17:38,690 --> 00:17:42,995
Is he annoying, infuriating,
or maybe you just don't care?

237
00:17:49,601 --> 00:17:50,536
I can't forgive him.

238
00:17:53,639 --> 00:17:55,007
That's understandable.

239
00:17:56,375 --> 00:17:57,443
I'm sure you can't.

240
00:18:00,145 --> 00:18:02,548
But I don't think
you need to hold back those feelings.

241
00:18:03,649 --> 00:18:07,119
At Yukanai, you’re free
to spend your time however you like.

242
00:18:08,854 --> 00:18:10,556
If you’re tired, you can just sleep.

243
00:18:12,658 --> 00:18:13,859
Why not come and check it out?

244
00:18:16,295 --> 00:18:17,963
If you don't like it, you can leave.

245
00:18:19,164 --> 00:18:19,998
How does that sound?

246
00:18:25,804 --> 00:18:28,573
All right, it’s time for our annual
Yukanai festival!

247
00:18:28,574 --> 00:18:30,274
What kind of festival
would you like to have this year?

248
00:18:30,275 --> 00:18:31,175
Yakisoba festival.

249
00:18:31,176 --> 00:18:32,376
Baseball tournament.

250
00:18:32,377 --> 00:18:33,811
I really want to play baseball.

251
00:18:33,812 --> 00:18:35,079
I want a giant paella.

252
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,914
- Mochitsuki festival.
- Great Detective Saku.

253
00:18:36,915 --> 00:18:38,282
Don't speak all at once.

254
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:40,184
- Paella.
- I can't hear everyone at once.

255
00:18:40,185 --> 00:18:41,652
Mochitsuki festival.

256
00:18:41,653 --> 00:18:43,154
Mochitsuki sounds fun.

257
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:44,556
What do you want to do, Tatsuki?

258
00:18:47,192 --> 00:18:48,292
Let's see…

259
00:18:48,293 --> 00:18:50,328
Your energy is so low, Tatsuki.

260
00:18:50,329 --> 00:18:51,929
Yeah, let's get pumped up.

261
00:18:51,930 --> 00:18:52,898
Sorry, I spaced out.

262
00:18:54,766 --> 00:18:56,401
Great Detective Sakura.

263
00:19:01,473 --> 00:19:03,341
- Welcome back.
- Thank you.

264
00:19:03,342 --> 00:19:05,309
How's Sora?

265
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:06,812
He's in his room right now.

266
00:19:08,113 --> 00:19:09,847
I actually just asked Sora

267
00:19:09,848 --> 00:19:12,384
if he'd like to go to Yukanai with me.

268
00:19:13,318 --> 00:19:14,619
Would that be all right?

269
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:16,488
- To Yukanai?
- Yes.

270
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:19,758
I'm okay with it if he wants to go.

271
00:19:25,631 --> 00:19:27,432
All right, we'll be off.

272
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,268
I'll contact you later.

273
00:19:30,636 --> 00:19:31,802
Okay.

274
00:19:31,803 --> 00:19:33,504
Please take this chance to rest.

275
00:19:33,505 --> 00:19:34,606
Bye.

276
00:19:35,507 --> 00:19:36,375
Let's go.

277
00:19:47,085 --> 00:19:49,220
Raise your hands for the paella.

278
00:19:49,221 --> 00:19:52,657
- Raise your hand.
- Raise your hand for the paella.

279
00:19:52,658 --> 00:19:55,493
- One, two, three…
- Everyone, raise your hand.

280
00:19:55,494 --> 00:19:56,861
Raise your hand.

281
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,296
Seriously?

282
00:19:58,297 --> 00:19:59,898
Come inside.

283
00:20:04,903 --> 00:20:06,337
That's a lot of people.

284
00:20:06,338 --> 00:20:08,273
One, two, three, four, five…

285
00:20:22,087 --> 00:20:24,255
Who wants to vote for baseball?

286
00:20:24,256 --> 00:20:26,457
At Yukanai, we decide everything
through meetings.

287
00:20:26,458 --> 00:20:28,359
You can do whatever you want here.

288
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:30,294
Paella!

289
00:20:30,295 --> 00:20:32,931
Hide-and-seek.

290
00:20:35,334 --> 00:20:38,070
I thought it might be better
than being stuck at home.

291
00:20:49,214 --> 00:20:51,516
Hey Shi-chan. Who's that?

292
00:20:52,017 --> 00:20:53,718
Is that a new student?

293
00:20:53,719 --> 00:20:54,685
His name is Sora.

294
00:20:54,686 --> 00:20:55,954
Is he nervous?

295
00:20:57,756 --> 00:20:58,656
Maybe.

296
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:01,092
- Okay, I'm going to talk to him.
- I'll go too.

297
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:01,993
Me too.

298
00:21:01,994 --> 00:21:03,261
Let's go.

299
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:04,696
Hello. Did you join today?

300
00:21:06,465 --> 00:21:07,733
Let's have a kick-up competition.

301
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:10,368
One, two…

302
00:21:10,369 --> 00:21:12,270
What're you doing?

303
00:21:12,271 --> 00:21:14,705
What's wrong with you?

304
00:21:14,706 --> 00:21:16,841
I, Riri the Witch,
shall cast a magic spell

305
00:21:16,842 --> 00:21:18,677
to lift your spirits!

306
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:24,216
It didn't work.

307
00:21:24,916 --> 00:21:26,584
We apologize, please excuse us.

308
00:21:26,585 --> 00:21:27,719
Sorry.

309
00:21:33,558 --> 00:21:34,493
Here you go.

310
00:21:34,993 --> 00:21:35,927
Thanks.

311
00:21:38,397 --> 00:21:40,499
How did the "sharing" go with Ms. Yu?

312
00:21:40,999 --> 00:21:42,467
Thank you for that.

313
00:21:43,235 --> 00:21:45,804
I thought I really understood Sora,

314
00:21:46,938 --> 00:21:49,374
but it turns out
there’s still so much I don't know.

315
00:21:50,776 --> 00:21:52,009
I wanted you two

316
00:21:52,010 --> 00:21:55,012
to share your feelings for Sora
with each other

317
00:21:55,013 --> 00:21:57,416
by going through
his photos and his artwork.

318
00:21:59,418 --> 00:22:02,887
First, I wanted you two
to get away from all the pain,

319
00:22:02,888 --> 00:22:05,057
in order to find
even a little bit of peace.

320
00:22:06,892 --> 00:22:07,726
Um…

321
00:22:08,593 --> 00:22:10,696
Why is Sora here?

322
00:22:12,264 --> 00:22:15,033
I ended up bringing him here
a bit forcefully. Sorry.

323
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:16,567
Not at all.

324
00:22:16,568 --> 00:22:20,204
I hope it helps take his mind off things,
even if only a little.

325
00:22:20,205 --> 00:22:21,373
Yeah.

326
00:22:23,442 --> 00:22:25,744
What is it that Sora likes most right now?

327
00:22:26,545 --> 00:22:29,013
What Sora likes the most right now?

328
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:31,717
Things like hobbies,
or something he's good at.

329
00:22:42,894 --> 00:22:45,230
I don't know.

330
00:22:46,331 --> 00:22:48,233
It's all right.

331
00:22:52,437 --> 00:22:54,405
Ding dong.

332
00:22:54,406 --> 00:22:56,340
Attention Mr. Tatsuki.

333
00:22:56,341 --> 00:22:57,476
Please gather in the garden.

334
00:22:58,610 --> 00:23:00,946
- Okay.
- Ding dong.

335
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:06,183
Have fun.

336
00:23:06,184 --> 00:23:07,018
Okay.

337
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:09,954
What is it?

338
00:23:09,955 --> 00:23:12,189
- Let's go, Tatsuki.
- Let's go.

339
00:23:12,190 --> 00:23:14,226
- Yeah, I'm coming.
- Hurry.

340
00:23:23,168 --> 00:23:24,969
- Want this couch?
- No.

341
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:26,271
No, sit down.

342
00:23:32,544 --> 00:23:35,046
- Tatsuki!
- This way.

343
00:23:37,215 --> 00:23:39,718
Nice! Yeah!

344
00:23:48,126 --> 00:23:50,394
- I did it!
- Congratulations!

345
00:23:50,395 --> 00:23:51,596
I did it!

346
00:23:53,331 --> 00:23:55,834
- I'm so glad.
- You did it, Sora.

347
00:24:03,842 --> 00:24:05,911
Hey, can you draw a gorilla?

348
00:24:27,432 --> 00:24:29,366
He's wasting water.

349
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:31,102
Isn't Tatsuki acting strange?

350
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:33,704
He's feeling down.

351
00:24:33,705 --> 00:24:36,208
It's like his soul has left his body.

352
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:39,177
He's forcing himself to smile.

353
00:24:41,079 --> 00:24:44,181
At times like this,
we should cheer him up, huh?

354
00:24:44,182 --> 00:24:46,151
What can we do for him?

355
00:24:49,287 --> 00:24:51,656
I wonder what they're discussing?

356
00:24:55,527 --> 00:24:56,528
Shi-chan?

357
00:24:59,264 --> 00:25:01,633
I wonder what I can do to help.

358
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:05,871
Yeah, I wonder too.

359
00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:13,311
How about we use the festival
to cheer him up?

360
00:25:14,145 --> 00:25:15,279
Good idea.

361
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:17,315
But we haven't decided on what to do yet.

362
00:25:18,116 --> 00:25:20,084
He's terrible at sports,

363
00:25:20,085 --> 00:25:21,385
so the baseball tournament is out.

364
00:25:21,386 --> 00:25:22,686
‎Yeah.

365
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:23,921
No dodgeball either.

366
00:25:23,922 --> 00:25:25,991
- Right.
- He doesn't like yakisoba either.

367
00:25:26,558 --> 00:25:27,458
Really?

368
00:25:27,459 --> 00:25:29,427
Then what should we do?

369
00:25:32,063 --> 00:25:32,898
What about music?

370
00:25:34,766 --> 00:25:37,935
Good idea. Tatsuki will get excited
if we have a music festival.

371
00:25:37,936 --> 00:25:40,271
Sounds good.
We can split up into a few teams,

372
00:25:40,272 --> 00:25:42,006
like for a band or a dance group.

373
00:25:42,007 --> 00:25:42,907
That'll be fun.

374
00:25:42,908 --> 00:25:45,409
All right,
let's go with the music festival.

375
00:25:45,410 --> 00:25:47,512
- Let's do it.
- Yeah.

376
00:25:53,919 --> 00:25:55,120
Tatsuki.

377
00:25:58,557 --> 00:26:00,392
We decided to have a music festival.

378
00:26:01,359 --> 00:26:02,627
I see.

379
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:04,429
Are you excited?

380
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:06,798
Yeah. I'm excited.

381
00:26:07,899 --> 00:26:09,334
You don't seem it.

382
00:26:10,435 --> 00:26:11,536
Oh well.

383
00:26:14,539 --> 00:26:15,473
What is it?

384
00:26:18,343 --> 00:26:20,211
The guy that came in today…

385
00:26:23,014 --> 00:26:24,482
Is he your son?

386
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:31,489
How did you know?

387
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:37,629
Because whenever a new student arrives,
you always go up to them first.

388
00:26:38,763 --> 00:26:40,531
But you didn't do that today.

389
00:26:40,532 --> 00:26:41,933
I see.

390
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:46,738
Things are still tense?

391
00:26:50,942 --> 00:26:54,579
Well, it won't be easy to mend things.

392
00:26:56,381 --> 00:26:58,483
You should help him the way you helped us.

393
00:27:00,218 --> 00:27:01,786
It's complicated.

394
00:27:04,623 --> 00:27:05,857
Okay,

395
00:27:06,891 --> 00:27:08,360
I guess I'll step in to help out.

396
00:27:09,594 --> 00:27:11,495
No, it's all right.

397
00:27:11,496 --> 00:27:13,231
- Really.
- Don't you worry.

398
00:27:13,832 --> 00:27:15,433
Don't be like that.

399
00:27:15,934 --> 00:27:18,102
Please let me repay the favor.

400
00:27:18,103 --> 00:27:19,371
What's going on?

401
00:27:23,041 --> 00:27:25,175
- Bye Shi-chan.
- Bye.

402
00:27:25,176 --> 00:27:27,946
- Bye.
- See you.

403
00:27:29,114 --> 00:27:30,515
Let's walk back together.

404
00:27:31,850 --> 00:27:33,317
Oh, I forgot something.

405
00:27:33,318 --> 00:27:34,752
You forgot something?

406
00:27:34,753 --> 00:27:36,053
You passed me.

407
00:27:36,054 --> 00:27:37,856
What should I do now?

408
00:27:39,157 --> 00:27:41,825
- Wow. This is very good.
- Yeah.

409
00:27:41,826 --> 00:27:43,395
Sora drew this for me.

410
00:27:44,129 --> 00:27:45,230
Oh, really?

411
00:27:48,833 --> 00:27:50,768
- Bye.
- Bye.

412
00:27:50,769 --> 00:27:51,669
Take care.

413
00:27:51,670 --> 00:27:53,705
- Good.
- It won't move.

414
00:27:54,639 --> 00:27:55,707
Oh no.

415
00:27:56,207 --> 00:27:57,541
I keep falling.

416
00:27:57,542 --> 00:27:58,510
Why?

417
00:28:00,278 --> 00:28:02,079
What's going on?

418
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:04,182
- You can do it.
- It's okay.

419
00:28:05,450 --> 00:28:06,884
- Soya.
- Yeah?

420
00:28:06,885 --> 00:28:08,018
I'm going to step out.

421
00:28:08,019 --> 00:28:09,954
Oh okay.

422
00:28:11,022 --> 00:28:11,922
FUJINAGA

423
00:28:11,923 --> 00:28:14,191
- A manga?
- Yes.

424
00:28:14,192 --> 00:28:16,894
His drawing was very good, so I wondered

425
00:28:16,895 --> 00:28:20,031
if maybe he actually enjoyed
drawing manga?

426
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:23,401
He used to draw them quite often
until a while ago.

427
00:28:24,903 --> 00:28:27,038
Do you have any of those manga?

428
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:30,275
I'm not sure.

429
00:28:30,775 --> 00:28:33,177
There might be some in his room,

430
00:28:33,178 --> 00:28:35,379
but I'm not sure where it went
after the move.

431
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:38,550
No problem.
I was just wondering, that's all.

432
00:28:44,956 --> 00:28:47,058
It might be here.

433
00:28:50,195 --> 00:28:52,330
Why do you need his manga?

434
00:28:52,831 --> 00:28:53,765
Oh…

435
00:28:54,265 --> 00:28:56,033
By delving deep into the things

436
00:28:56,034 --> 00:28:59,036
that Sora liked, or was passionate about,

437
00:28:59,037 --> 00:29:01,138
we can sometimes catch a glimpse
of the feelings

438
00:29:01,139 --> 00:29:02,907
hidden deep within his heart.

439
00:29:04,275 --> 00:29:06,611
- Is that right?
- Yes.

440
00:29:15,887 --> 00:29:17,288
What's that…?

441
00:29:19,324 --> 00:29:21,126
He ripped it up himself.

442
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:25,463
<i>It was around the time
he stopped going to school.</i>

443
00:29:35,874 --> 00:29:38,409
To tear up something that he loved…

444
00:29:41,212 --> 00:29:42,781
He must've been struggling a lot.

445
00:29:47,819 --> 00:29:50,088
But I could do nothing but panic.

446
00:29:50,588 --> 00:29:52,023
I couldn't do anything to help.

447
00:29:54,859 --> 00:29:56,427
I'm so pathetic.

448
00:30:05,403 --> 00:30:07,405
You're not pathetic.

449
00:30:09,874 --> 00:30:12,076
You carefully kept all the things

450
00:30:12,677 --> 00:30:14,012
from his childhood

451
00:30:14,579 --> 00:30:16,681
like his artwork, and his manga.

452
00:30:18,216 --> 00:30:20,418
I can truly feel the love you have

453
00:30:21,286 --> 00:30:22,387
for Sora.

454
00:30:27,091 --> 00:30:31,296
I too, spent my middle
and high school years as a shut-in.

455
00:30:33,031 --> 00:30:35,733
I caused my parents a great deal of worry.

456
00:30:37,569 --> 00:30:40,805
There were times
when I was so anxious and irritable

457
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:44,909
that I even lashed out and cursed at them.

458
00:30:46,344 --> 00:30:48,746
But my parents
simply watched over me patiently.

459
00:30:50,148 --> 00:30:51,549
And I'm so grateful to them.

460
00:30:54,586 --> 00:30:58,590
I believe that someday
Sora will feel the same way about you.

461
00:30:59,257 --> 00:31:00,725
So

462
00:31:02,427 --> 00:31:04,529
please don't be too harsh on yourself.

463
00:31:12,370 --> 00:31:15,173
It won't do any good
if I can't stay strong.

464
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:20,845
Um…

465
00:31:21,512 --> 00:31:24,883
May I borrow that?

466
00:31:29,153 --> 00:31:29,988
Yes.

467
00:31:49,641 --> 00:31:50,608
You're awake?

468
00:31:56,114 --> 00:31:57,315
Do you know <i>Brave Drop</i>?

469
00:31:58,683 --> 00:31:59,784
Have you ever played it?

470
00:32:01,386 --> 00:32:02,286
Yeah.

471
00:32:02,287 --> 00:32:05,089
Really? Can you help me out?

472
00:32:21,873 --> 00:32:22,874
What's your name?

473
00:32:25,376 --> 00:32:26,244
Sora.

474
00:32:28,913 --> 00:32:30,248
I'm Tomoki.

475
00:32:34,419 --> 00:32:36,788
- Hey Shi-chan.
- I'm back.

476
00:32:46,898 --> 00:32:47,799
Mr. Tatsuki.

477
00:32:49,734 --> 00:32:51,436
Do you have a minute?

478
00:33:01,512 --> 00:33:03,213
What's this?

479
00:33:03,214 --> 00:33:05,616
It's Sora's manga notebook.

480
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:10,153
When he was in middle school,

481
00:33:10,154 --> 00:33:12,390
around the time
when he stopped going to school,

482
00:33:13,057 --> 00:33:15,093
he apparently tore it up himself.

483
00:33:39,283 --> 00:33:41,886
I never knew he had been drawing so much.

484
00:33:43,154 --> 00:33:46,557
Right now, the pages
are all scattered and unreadable…

485
00:33:48,326 --> 00:33:50,094
but why don't we try
piecing them back together?

486
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:55,133
I was just wondering if, perhaps,

487
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:57,167
Sora's bottled-up feelings

488
00:33:57,168 --> 00:33:59,737
might be hidden somewhere
within this manga.

489
00:34:00,905 --> 00:34:02,607
It's just a thought.

490
00:34:10,148 --> 00:34:10,982
I'll give it a try.

491
00:34:12,183 --> 00:34:13,418
I'll help out too.

492
00:34:14,752 --> 00:34:16,186
I may not look it,

493
00:34:16,187 --> 00:34:18,089
but I'm actually pretty good
at jigsaw puzzles.

494
00:34:26,798 --> 00:34:28,066
What do you think

495
00:34:30,568 --> 00:34:31,736
about Tatsuki?

496
00:34:38,676 --> 00:34:39,610
Nothing really…

497
00:34:41,279 --> 00:34:42,313
Nothing in particular.

498
00:34:45,817 --> 00:34:46,951
I see.

499
00:34:49,087 --> 00:34:50,388
It doesn't matter anyway.

500
00:34:53,825 --> 00:34:54,859
I see.

501
00:34:58,229 --> 00:34:59,797
Maybe it's because he's your dad.

502
00:35:02,733 --> 00:35:03,668
What do you mean?

503
00:35:06,537 --> 00:35:08,339
Everyone here

504
00:35:09,907 --> 00:35:11,609
loves Tatsuki.

505
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:16,681
Why?

506
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:19,350
How should I put it…?

507
00:35:23,187 --> 00:35:26,257
We're pretty messed up,

508
00:35:28,926 --> 00:35:30,928
but he accepts everything about us.

509
00:35:32,597 --> 00:35:34,532
And he always has our backs.

510
00:35:35,666 --> 00:35:36,701
Are you sure

511
00:35:38,035 --> 00:35:39,370
you're not being fooled?

512
00:35:41,873 --> 00:35:43,508
He's not really that nice of a guy.

513
00:35:45,610 --> 00:35:46,611
Is that right?

514
00:35:52,283 --> 00:35:53,251
It's over.

515
00:35:57,421 --> 00:35:58,589
You can still keep going.

516
00:35:59,223 --> 00:36:00,992
There's a shortcut ahead.

517
00:36:14,405 --> 00:36:16,240
You weren't talking about the game?

518
00:36:18,142 --> 00:36:19,210
It's nothing.

519
00:36:31,355 --> 00:36:32,557
Sora,

520
00:36:35,526 --> 00:36:37,028
I think we're alike.

521
00:36:38,930 --> 00:36:39,864
‎What?

522
00:36:42,967 --> 00:36:43,834
Back when

523
00:36:46,003 --> 00:36:48,472
I was in my second year of middle school,
I got bullied.

524
00:36:51,676 --> 00:36:53,578
I stopped going to school

525
00:36:57,181 --> 00:36:59,317
and just spent all day in my room
playing video games.

526
00:37:02,620 --> 00:37:06,190
I couldn't understand my studies at all,

527
00:37:08,226 --> 00:37:10,261
and everyone around me
was talking about entrance exams…

528
00:37:13,898 --> 00:37:14,932
but I didn't feel like

529
00:37:16,934 --> 00:37:18,903
I was capable of going anywhere.

530
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:32,383
I thought, "My life is completely over."

531
00:37:35,720 --> 00:37:37,455
And I intended to kill myself.

532
00:37:42,226 --> 00:37:43,194
I was serious.

533
00:37:45,730 --> 00:37:46,697
I'm

534
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,101
going to end my life here.

535
00:37:51,936 --> 00:37:53,604
- What?
<i>- But…</i>

536
00:37:54,772 --> 00:37:56,807
Tatsuki came to stop me.

537
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:02,413
He told me not to end my life.

538
00:38:04,115 --> 00:38:05,449
He was so persistent.

539
00:38:11,756 --> 00:38:13,724
He said his son
tried to take his own life too…

540
00:38:16,427 --> 00:38:17,328
So

541
00:38:18,396 --> 00:38:21,499
he would never repeat
the same mistake again.

542
00:38:24,835 --> 00:38:26,804
Even after hearing that,

543
00:38:30,007 --> 00:38:31,575
I was serious about my decision.

544
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:36,480
- Bye.
- Tomoki!

545
00:38:37,048 --> 00:38:38,082
<i>Then…</i>

546
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:40,651
<i>while trying to save me,</i>

547
00:38:41,919 --> 00:38:43,721
<i>he fell down instead.</i>

548
00:38:47,491 --> 00:38:48,626
What?

549
00:38:50,161 --> 00:38:51,662
You normally couldn't

550
00:38:53,664 --> 00:38:55,599
do something like that, could you?

551
00:38:58,602 --> 00:39:00,705
Even though he was the one
who almost died,

552
00:39:01,839 --> 00:39:03,874
he was still worrying about me.

553
00:39:05,343 --> 00:39:06,644
Tomoki.

554
00:39:07,745 --> 00:39:09,080
I'm so glad

555
00:39:10,214 --> 00:39:11,382
you're alive.

556
00:39:13,617 --> 00:39:16,253
I was like, what's wrong with this guy?

557
00:39:29,367 --> 00:39:30,534
Tatsuki

558
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:34,538
is amazing.

559
00:39:41,779 --> 00:39:42,847
That can't be true.

560
00:39:48,319 --> 00:39:49,620
You can't believe it?

561
00:39:53,124 --> 00:39:55,259
He's not that kind of a guy at all.

562
00:40:01,165 --> 00:40:02,032
I see.

563
00:40:10,975 --> 00:40:13,344
I think this is the last one.

564
00:40:29,627 --> 00:40:31,395
We pieced it all together.

565
00:40:34,598 --> 00:40:36,400
I'll be going home now.

566
00:40:39,303 --> 00:40:40,237
Thank you.

567
00:40:58,088 --> 00:40:59,390
Should we call it a day?

568
00:41:04,695 --> 00:41:05,796
Okay.

569
00:41:12,236 --> 00:41:15,339
It's all right. I'll do the rest.

570
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:19,343
Sora,

571
00:41:20,644 --> 00:41:22,213
you have something else to do, right?

572
00:41:40,498 --> 00:41:41,731
SEASHELL

573
00:41:41,732 --> 00:41:43,066
IT'S A PRETTY SEASHELL

574
00:41:43,067 --> 00:41:44,335
WHAT A BEAUTIFUL SOUND

575
00:41:47,071 --> 00:41:48,404
Here, this is for you.

576
00:41:48,405 --> 00:41:49,839
It's pretty.

577
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:51,442
Okay, Dad, let's race.

578
00:42:11,862 --> 00:42:12,796
This

579
00:42:13,831 --> 00:42:14,965
is nice.

580
00:42:17,868 --> 00:42:18,836
You

581
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:21,272
liked drawing manga?

582
00:42:27,578 --> 00:42:30,247
I never knew you had put in so much effort

583
00:42:31,415 --> 00:42:32,883
drawing manga like this.

584
00:42:39,557 --> 00:42:41,125
Sora, it's okay

585
00:42:41,959 --> 00:42:43,227
for you to do whatever

586
00:42:44,528 --> 00:42:45,596
you want to do.

587
00:42:51,101 --> 00:42:53,437
You're saying that for real?

588
00:42:55,205 --> 00:42:57,942
What if I end up
turning into a good-for-nothing adult?

589
00:43:00,044 --> 00:43:01,411
Who you are right now is what--

590
00:43:01,412 --> 00:43:02,980
That's just lip service.

591
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:05,516
Deep down,

592
00:43:06,617 --> 00:43:08,451
you really think I'm no good,

593
00:43:08,452 --> 00:43:09,352
don't you?

594
00:43:09,353 --> 00:43:10,788
No, never.

595
00:43:13,557 --> 00:43:14,959
Everyone's fawning over you

596
00:43:15,526 --> 00:43:16,961
yelling, "Tatsuki! Tatsuki!"

597
00:43:17,561 --> 00:43:18,629
So you're smiling like a fool

598
00:43:20,164 --> 00:43:21,532
letting it all go to your head.

599
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:24,735
Even with Tomoki…

600
00:43:26,670 --> 00:43:28,372
You risked your life to save him, right?

601
00:43:32,843 --> 00:43:33,811
Why…

602
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:36,113
Why…

603
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:38,182
Why do you risk your life

604
00:43:39,049 --> 00:43:40,851
to save others

605
00:43:42,419 --> 00:43:43,354
while I…

606
00:43:48,892 --> 00:43:50,794
While I've ended up like this…?

607
00:43:57,534 --> 00:43:59,136
- Why?
- Sora.

608
00:44:01,739 --> 00:44:05,609
You're acting like such a good guy
when you're actually a jerk.

609
00:44:06,343 --> 00:44:08,045
Stop putting up a front!

610
00:44:11,048 --> 00:44:13,617
Stop staring in silence and say something!

611
00:44:16,854 --> 00:44:17,955
Which one…

612
00:44:19,623 --> 00:44:20,824
Which one…

613
00:44:21,959 --> 00:44:24,461
Which one is the real you?

614
00:44:35,005 --> 00:44:38,908
PREVIEW OF THE NEXT EPISODE

615
00:44:38,909 --> 00:44:41,010
THIS DRAMA IS FICTIONAL

616
00:44:41,011 --> 00:44:41,945
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
